ok, after watching this thoroughly, I give the movie a 5/10. I'm a purist when it comes to books turned into movies, and this one is complete shit. 

It misses out the one thing that makes Jack Kerouac's book worth reading, his voice. The movie has no insights into sex, drugs, music or beatniks and it doesn't really have the flow or the suspense that the book carried with it. That being said, it's a decent movie if you separate it from being involved with the book.

Also, if you downloaded this just to see Kristen Stewarts tits, go fuck yourself.
